This is exactly like the gazpacho I ate in Spain. Seeding the tomatoes over a sieve and soaking the bread in the resulting tomato water creates more flavor and no seeds makes the final product easier to sieve. (Seeding and peeling makes the sieving a cinch.) Do try to get sherry vinegar; it makes a huge difference. Also, do sieve it. It really improves the texture. A professional chef tried mine, made exactly to the recipe, and served it in his restaurant.

